						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in a street of the village.</p>						

						<p>Records the construction of a Jaina temple at Munugōḍu, during the time of Muni Suvrata-Tīrtha. Further it records that some repairs are carried out by Bōya-Gaṭṭa, a servant of the king Goṅka in the same temple. In characters of 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
